title: Spatial distribution of e-waste in news-sphere
name: Spatial distribution of e-waste in news-sphere
description: The dataset was composed through geocoding of textual data in all of the articles on the topic of e-waste published online on Guardian, New York Times and Wired magazine. It shows the geospatial distribution of locative references that occur across these articles. E-waste is a term denoting discarded electronic devices. Website of the mapping e-waste project: http://igor.gold.ac.uk/~so301gb/workspace/index.html.
